# NewsLens environment — copy to `.env` (cp .env.example .env) and fill it in
# YOURSELF. Names + descriptions only live in this file; real values only ever
# live in .env, which is gitignored. Never paste a key into chat or a commit —
# if one leaks, rotate it at the provider immediately.
#
# After filling anything in, run `scripts/doctor` — it validates every value
# with harmless read-only calls and tells you exactly what's still missing.

# --- LLM generation (required) -----------------------------------------------
# Text generation (GPT-4o-mini) for the ranking / narrative / script steps.
# Get one at platform.openai.com/api-keys. Scope: standard API key, no special
# permissions beyond default usage — and set a hard monthly spend cap in the
# OpenAI dashboard (Settings -> Limits), not just in-app.
# NOTE on audio: the default TTS is gpt-4o-mini-tts on THIS key (~$0.015/min,
# ~+$0.07/run — your ear-test pick, 2026-07-06). Kokoro-82M local stays fully
# built as the $0 fallback: pin `settings.tts_engine: kokoro` in sources.yaml
# to use it. This key is needed for text generation regardless of the voice.
OPENAI_API_KEY=
# --- Claude provider seam (REQUIRED as of B2; the Claude API lane is live) ----
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is the credential for the Claude API lane. B2 flipped the
# rank, editor, and script seats to Claude Haiku 4.5 on this lane, so this key
# is now REQUIRED for a normal generate — those three seats cannot run without
# it (the doctor validates it read-only and FAILs the run if it's missing).
# Get one at console.anthropic.com/settings/keys. Scope: a standard API key;
# set a hard monthly spend cap in the Anthropic console. Never echoed or logged.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# Lane selection for the provider seam (all optional; unset = the default seat
# map — Haiku on the Claude api lane for rank/editor/script, GPT-4o on the api
# lane for the rest). NEWSLENS_LANE = api | subscription (global);
# NEWSLENS_LANE_<SEAT> (e.g. NEWSLENS_LANE_RANK) overrides one seat. Selecting a
# lane with no registered provider (subscription, until B3) FAILS LOUD naming
# the fix (never a silent wrong-lane call). NEWSLENS_LANE_FALLBACK=api is the
# opt-in that lets an unavailable lane fall to the api lane (needs a second
# lane; B3). Leave all three unset in normal operation.
NEWSLENS_LANE=
NEWSLENS_LANE_FALLBACK=

# --- Discovery beyond named sources (required for Tier 2 sourcing) ------------
# Perplexity Sonar API for the one capped discovery query per run ("what's
# happening today that isn't in my named sources"). Get one at
# perplexity.ai/settings/api. Pay-as-you-go — set a prepaid credit cap in the
# Perplexity dashboard as the real spend limit; BUDGET_CAP_USD_PER_RUN below
# is a secondary guard, not the primary one.
# Until this key exists, ingest runs RSS-only and says so — and the moment it
# lands, run `scripts/sonar_spike` (the pending reliability gate).
PERPLEXITY_API_KEY=

# --- Cost guardrails (required, no external account needed) -------------------
# Aborts any LLM-spending run (rank today; generate at M5) whose estimated
# cost exceeds this (USD).
# ENGINEERING.md-mandated guardrail against runaway/retry-loop costs.
# Unset = default 0.25 (M9 ruling 2026-07-06: cut from 0.50 as the cost
# condition on the Analyst; degradation ladder protects content quality —
# see config.py).
BUDGET_CAP_USD_PER_RUN=0.25

# --- Scheduling (DORMANT — v1 is on-demand only, DECISIONS.md 2026-07-03) -----
# Nothing reads this in v1: briefings generate when you ask, not on a timer.
# Kept (optional) because re-enabling scheduling is a decision away; if ever
# used, it's the local hour (0-23) a daily run would fire. Unset = default 6.
GENERATE_HOUR_LOCAL=6

# --- Optional fallback (not required for the v1 default path) -----------------
# Fallback discovery source ONLY if the Sonar reliability spike fails (that
# spike is still pending). Leave blank until then — narrowest-scope rule:
# don't grant a second paid API key while the primary is unproven-insufficient.
GNEWS_API_KEY=
